What is Travellers’ Choice?
Tripadvisor gives a Travellers’ Choice award to accommodations, attractions and restaurants that consistently earn great reviews from travellers and are ranked within the top 10% of properties on Tripadvisor.
About
Travellers' Choice
2024
See the Davidson Glacier up close, from the vantage point of our 30-foot Voyager Canoes. The Glacier Point Wilderness Safari brings you into the Alaskan Wilderness and gives you a true taste of Alaska. Your adventure begins at your cruise ship where we’ll board a high-speed vessel made for wildlife viewing en route to an Alaskan paradise. We’ll ply the waters of the deepest Fjord in North America with a naturalist guide, watching for whales, sea lions, porpoise, and many other species of marine wildlife. We land at Glacier Point and board our Safari Buses for a short drive over the terminal moraines. Our award-winning guides share with you the wonders of this Glacial Wilderness. A quarter mile hike will lead us to the iceberg-studded lake where we’ll paddle our canoes to the face of the glacier. This is an ideal family adventure and one you won’t soon forget!

  • Corliss B
    49 contributions
    This was one of my top favorite highlights of my trip!! From the boat ride, hike, and canoe closer to the glacier, the guides were very personable and gave a wealth of information about the wildlife, land, plants, and even the rocks! Glacier point is gorgeous and I enjoyed learning about the spruce tips and the Devil’s Club, with guides pointing it out during the short hike through the woods. We saw beautiful waterfalls, stellar sea lions, and of course the Davidson Glacier! One of my fav things was talking about the different kinds of rocks on the boat and all the guides were very friendly, funny, and just full of awesome knowledge. I highly recommend this tour for a healthy dose of adventure and epic beauty with friendly & knowledgeable tour guides, ensuring you have a great time! I would pay just to camp at Glacier Point, it is such a beautiful place!
    Review of: Glacier Point Wilderness Safari

  • ack114
    Severn, Maryland40 contributions
    My teenage girls and I went on this excursion and really enjoyed it. The boat ride out was informative. The guides were awesome once we got to the site. We enjoyed hearing about their backgrounds and how they lived out there off the grid for 6 months of the year. We didn’t know lunch would be served so there was waiting around when we got there and would have rather spent time at glacier. The hike was easy and not strenuous . If you have mobility issues I’d reconsider going because of the tree limbs and rocks. The canoes were fun. No wildlife seen while out there. We did stop to see the sea lions on way back. My only criticism is the name is misleading. It’s not a wildlife safari.
